Data Collection Method: Jamar Count Board (Unit # T-2850)
1) First UMC Preschool, Rankin Elementary & Mount Holly
Middle Schools are located less than one mile from the
studied intersection and were in session on the dates of
the count, as were all Gaston County Schools.
2) Pedestrians were observed and counted – none were
3) SB approach grade is +5% and NB, EB, & WB are -5%.
4) Area lighting was not present at the count location.
5) No highway construction was observed that impacted normal traffic patterns.
6) Data collection equipment was operating correctly at time of count.
7) Counters took breaks from 9:30 – 9:45 AM, 11:15 – 11:30 AM, and 3:15 – 3:45 PM. Data for these periods
8) Counter Notes: When the local schools open and close for the day, this intersection is almost gridlocked in
all directions. The schools’ crossing guard confirmed this is a regular occurrence on school days.
